    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place">Phila.</name>
                    <date when="1887-04-28">Apr. 28, '88.</date>
                    <name type="place">Mr. W. Whitman, Camden, N.J.</name>
                </dateline>
                <salute><hi rend="italic">Dear Sir:—</hi></salute>
            </opener>
            <p>We will receive your <choice>
                    <orig>acct</orig>
                    <reg>account</reg>
                </choice> by the "Br. Prince," now due from Liverpool, consigned to us for your <choice>
                    <abbr>acct</abbr>
                    <expan>account</expan>
                </choice>., one package containing apparel valued at £1.<ptr target="med.00826_n1"/> We would thank you for
                your invoice covering same as early as possible in order to clear through customs on
                arrival. The package will come to us through the medium of Messrs. G. W. Wheatley
                &amp; Co. If the apparel contained therein is worn at all, kindly say so when
                replying to the above; and oblige</p>
            <closer>
                <salute>Yours truly</salute>
                <signed>O. G. Hempstead &amp; Son.</signed>
            </closer>
        </body>
    </text>
